<br>
Bargeroth<br>
&quot;who just wishes bards would be bards and wizards would be wizards and clerics would be clerics and leave the fighting to us men damn it&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ugozaro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gozaro</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.trafficblast.com/lott/data/gozaro_head.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#993300>(2/16/01 9:58:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help starting a warrior</span><hr size=1> Ogre or Troll.<br>
<br>
Ogres have the best base STR and STA and can't be stunded from the front by melee attack.<br>
Trolls get a nice natural regen and have good base STR and STA.<br>
<br>
You'll be fine as a barbarian and it will be nice not being kos everywhere.  I personally never go anywhere since I have a druid on a seperate account.<br>
I'm basically of the belief that when it all said and done all warriors pretty much want to be wearing the same thing.  Those that aren't Ogre or troll will have to equip items to make up for their lack of STR and STA stats.<br>
<br>
I played a Halfling warrior to 47 and then switched to OGRE because of that.  <br>
<br>
Gozaro is 56 and he's like the &quot;fridge&quot; when it comes to defense.  That's another reason for this mentality.  Warriors are defenders.  Sure we can out damage hybrids, and pets, but our job is to take the hits.<br>
<br>
I personally think you should play what you want, but if you want to play the &quot;best&quot; warrior go with troll or ogre.<br>
<br>
I see warriors duel to see who is better, but in my book the only way to prove who is the better warrior is to grab a 60 monk and see which one takes loggest to kill =)<br>
<br>
Hope that helps..<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ueuthanasiawarrior.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euth Anasia Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#993300>(2/16/01 10:13:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help starting a warrior</span><hr size=1> It depends on how ya want to live quite honestly.  I chose Barbarian so I could go into the majority of the towns and I still had the bash skill.  I played a Half Elf warrior, and ive played a Halfling Warrior.  Yea, they are fun yadday yadda yadda....but at higher levels, interrupting a MOB's casting is WAY to important in my opinion.  There have been many fights where a casting MOB hasnt even got off one spell.  So, since I like to go to cities, and think that bash is EXTREMELY important (if not essential) I chose barbarian :)  Hope that helps :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uzeniabigbootea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zenia Bigbootea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#993300>(2/16/01 10:45:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help starting a warrior</span><hr size=1> accept no substitutes, troll or ogre!!<br>
<br>
i myself prefer troll, cause of the minor size downgrade, and regen, although fire resist is a bit of a pain to get up :)<br>
<br>
but seriously, barbs are nice and all, but they just don't stand up to the raw power of an orge or a troll... IMO!<br>
